segment.source: Field Medic Appx
segment.target: Field Medic Appx

segment.source: Locate FieldMedic.appx with the MobileOS packages.
segment.target: Locate FieldMedic.appx with the MobileOS packages.

segment.source: Change the name of FieldMedic.appx to FieldMedic.zip.
segment.target: Change the name of FieldMedic.appx to FieldMedic.zip.

segment.source: Open FieldMedic.zip, and then open the ProfileXMLs folder.
segment.target: Open FieldMedic.zip, and then open the ProfileXMLs folder.

segment.source: In the ProfileXMLs folder, open any profile XML file to see the GUIDs of the ETW providers that belong to the profile.
segment.target: In the ProfileXMLs folder, open any profile XML file to see the GUIDs of the ETW providers that belong to the profile.

segment.source: For example, open FieldMedic-Performance.xml.
segment.target: For example, open FieldMedic-Performance.xml.

segment.source: Manifest files in the Windows Driver Kit
segment.target: Manifest files in the Windows Driver Kit

segment.source: Locate the Manifests folder in the Windows Driver Kit.
segment.target: Locate the Manifests folder in the Windows Driver Kit.

segment.source: Example: C:Program Files (x86)Windows Kits10Manifests
segment.target: Example: C:Program Files (x86)Windows Kits10Manifests

segment.source: In the Manifests folder, open any manifest (.mc) file to see the ETW provider name and GUID.
segment.target: In the Manifests folder, open any manifest (.mc) file to see the ETW provider name and GUID.

segment.source: For example, open microsoft-windowsphone-mtp.mc.
segment.target: For example, open microsoft-windowsphone-mtp.mc.
